The paper deals with entropy functionals and concentration inequalities for random matrices, which are topics that are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and data science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the subadditivity property of these entropy functionals, which is a topic that is relevant to both information theory and optimization (cs.SI). Finally, the paper derives several matrix concentration inequalities, which is a topic that is relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
